metadata.name: Inner Perception #58
metadata.description:
Each generated artwork of this collection showcases a different perspective on a single scene. The collection highlights the diversity and subjectivity of human perception, revealing how our individual experiences, perspectives, and interpretations shape the way we see the world. "Inner Perception" invites viewers to reflect on their own perspectives and promotes a deeper understanding of the impact that personal interpretation has on shaping our perceptions of reality.

Use buttons ("2" - 4000px, "3" - 8000px, "4" - 12000px, "5" - 16000px) to change canvas size and "s" to download image as PNG

Created with p5.js

metadata.name: Act One #267
metadata.description:
Act One, where the mannequin says ‚Äútake me home and I will dance for you forever‚Äù.

This work is an exploration of using motion capture data to create digital paintings, and a little belated birthday ballet for #fxhashturnsone. 
20% of primary sales are donated to Three.js.
 
Keyboard Controls:
[P] Play / pause the dance. By default the dance is paused after a few seconds to render a painting.
[S] Save the current view (live mode).
[V] Capture a short webm video (live mode).

Mouse Controls (while dancing): 
[left drag] Rotate
[scroll] Zoom
[right drag] Pan
[right click] Save image

Best viewed in a desktop browser. The output may be different from the preview image if your frame rate is low, reducing the size of the browser window can help improve the frame rate.

Made using Three.js, canvas API and WebGL2.
The 3D model is based on https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/mannequin-dances-ballet-a24678a81a6f4b6d8f8ba0eb1a78e58b, using motion capture data from dancedb.eu. 
Test in Chrome v107.0.5304.107 and Safari v16.1.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 2.0

Created by elsif, 2022.11.

metadata.name: L-Template #403
metadata.description:
THIS IS NOT AN ARTWORK.

Instead: a framework to store artwork data components onchain by including them as features in the token's smart contract. The stored data are parameters of a Lindenmayer System, which is a formal grammar that was initially conceived of as a theory of plant growth. L-Systems can model complex forms of plants using relatively few simple rules. Custom rules are generated during the minting of each token, based on the transaction hash string. 

The idea is that each iteration of the artwork can be reproduced accurately using an L-System interpreter by accessing the tezos blockchain through the FxHash API (GraphQL) and interpreting token metadata.

Reusable template source: https://github.com/x-terrain/x-terrain.github.io/tree/main/L-Template

Part of an ongoing project with RefractionDAO

metadata.name: fx(mash) #18
metadata.description:
fx(mash) is my humble contribution to celebrating #fxhashturnsone

This series is based on a simple algorithm - lines of a random length are drawn on a square grid until the grid is full.

I have added a variety of features based on some of my favorite fxhash projects and a few special guests.

This collection is intentionally diverse and disorderly, that's a nice way of saying I only had a short period of time following the release of Acequia. As a result, some of the outputs might be weird, messy, or even bordering on broken (if you get one of the latter please let me know and I'll reimburse you).

Despite being a bit rough around the edges, I hope fx(mash) reflects some measure of my love for the fxhash community. If you're feeling kind, then perhaps it even harks back to the experimental early days :)

The last year has been an incredible journey, thank you for letting me be a part of our story so far.

Controls (in live view):

- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [g] to toggle grain
- Press [h] for a high-res output

Beta Controls (in live view, definitely not fully tested):

- Press [p] to start/pause animation
- Press [i] to slow down animation
- Press [o] to speed up animation

All primary sales go to Savepakistan.


Acknowledgements:

fx(mash) uses Gorilla Sun's grain implementation, a big thanks to him and meezwhite for a great article that is well worth supporting https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

metadata.name: Gkrint #194
metadata.description:
Gkrint is a celebration of minimalism, colour, and space using the humble grid, a foundation of generative art, and movement. Through this collaboration, Ballzerino and George explore the relationships between these elements.

Inspired by the timeless principles of Bauhaus design, Ballzerino carefully curated custom colour palettes and selected geometric shapes, while George encoded the creative process into an algorithm, bringing the compositions to life, and putting the CPU to work finding new and unexpected compositions within our framework.

Gkrint is Ballzerino's genesis generative art drop.

Controls:
SPACE - pause / resume
click (or tap) - change colour selection (within same palette)
hold 'f' - speed up animation

Tested on Windows / Mac / iOS / Android. Chrome recommended for the best experience.

metadata.name: Kralen #153
metadata.description:
The outputs created by this algorithm reminded me of the colourful bead mazes that children play with. So, I named the algorithm 'Kralen', which means 'beads' in Dutch.

The algorithm 'Kralen' creates random bezier curves using the edges of a rectangular boundary, and places beads atop these curves to create a 'bead maze' effect. The algorithm offers different curve creation modes, with the most common mode being 'Mix'. In this mode, two random edges of the boundary are chosen to form bezier curves. Other modes create curves that are horizontally or vertically oriented, or formed using only the corners of the boundary

---

The work is created with p5.js with the help of bezier.js for working with bezier curves.

metadata.name: YYYSEED #794
metadata.description:
üî• BURN NOTICE: This is a FIVE DAY "open edition" to celebrate the launch of fx(params). The project is open for minting from the start of Monday until midnight Friday (GMT).

YYYSEED is an artwork with an aesthetic that works across digital, print and pen plotting mediums, leaning towards the minimalistic nature of drawing machines. SVGs can be exported for this purpose.

I've designed the algorithm to work best for this with the default settings, you should be good to go right out of the box. You can explore the design space a little further using the parameters (more details below).

If you're planning on plotting the work at larger sizes (A2, A1), then the "Override suggest lines" is there for you to cram more of them into the extra space.

PARAMS ::::::::::::::

The initial settings of the parameters are what I think best for the look I'm trying to achieve as the artist: minimal pen plotting work. This comes from the "Suggested" and "Random for hash" values.

You can take the design away from that by turning the "Use suggested lines" and "Use suggested destroyer" options off, and using your own values with the slider.

"Random for hash" means the feature has been randomly selected and fixed for the current hash and won't change. For example, if the hash is 'ooABCD' and the grid's "Random for hash" picks 3x4, then it will always be 3x4 for that hash, it isn't random each time you change sometime. Picking a new hash however will then randomly pick a new (fixed) option.

DANGER SEED :::::::::

USE OF THE DANGER SEED IS NOT RECOMMENDED. If you set the DANGER SEED, the value will be encoded along with the rest of the params (where it can be decoded) in the stored data of the mint, along with the token.

The DANGER SEED will only take effect if it starts with 'YYY', it will STOMP all over the other settings, including the hash.

INSTRUCTIONS ::::::::

h - Toggle highres mode on/off (starts off)
t - Toggle paper background on/off
s - Save png (in highres if toggled on)
1-6 - Save SVGs for plotting A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, A6

PEN PLOTTING ::::::::

Press 1-6 to select which A1-6 size paper you want to plot onto, the the system will download one or more files for you to use, one file per colour.

Please tag #plottertwitter, or #penplotter on twitter, instagram & mastodon

PRINTING ::::::::::::

The output of the high resolution version is 6,144 x 8,192 pixels. That will print at the following sizes.

300dpi: 20.48 x 27.31 inches (52.02 x 69.35 cm)
200dpi: 30.72 x 40.96 inches (78.03 x 104.03 cm)

300dpi is recommended, but 200dpi should be fine for this design. I suggest turning the paper texture off if you're printing onto textured archival paper, you can leave it on when printing onto smooth white paper.

metadata.name: Asemic writing #3
metadata.description:
This piece is an expanse on my piece for Genuary 2023 "Asemic".

Amidst the cacophony of our mundane language, a new form of expression arises. Each stroke of ink, each fluid line, each curve and shape, has its own unique voice. Breathing life into the seemingly meaningless, each output is its own language, with its own message for us to interpret and read as we see it. All set on a rich paperlike generated texture.

Asemic writing is a visual form of expression that combines elements of writing and art. It transcends traditional linguistic boundaries, using fluid lines, shapes, and curves to suggest meaning and emotion.

Primary Giving
20% Girls Who Code

Interactions:
T = Toggle background textures
S = Save image
R = Replay writing

metadata.name: 23050101_Loop.png #4
metadata.description:
Description:

Computers are operated by various layers of programs such as operating systems, middleware, and applications interacting with each other. In the past, some operating systems were prolonged. Such OSs sometimes froze with the mouse cursor tracing on the screen. In this artwork, one of the causes of program freezes, such as "Loop" in programs (e.g., "for" and "while" constructs), is represented by the circular trajectory of the mouse cursor as a "Loop".

Features:

[S] ... Save the image.
[R] ... Redraw the image.
[I] ... Toggle information displays.

metadata.name: Release #64
metadata.description:
[‚Ä¶]

More than anything she had wanted to show him where she had lived, where, at a specific time every year, endless fields sent a new cycle of pods on their way.

She preferred to experience these moments alone, imagining the spectacle was being performed just for her. The whole act carried a promise of new beginnings, of paths yet to be taken.

She wasn't really part of any of this, but she too had the coordinates to her own life programmed into her genes.

Any decision would be true now, any path free.

A chorus of explosions sounded as the field burst open.

[‚Ä¶]

‚Äì

You can append these parameters to the URL:

[scale=<number>] scale the renderer.
[long-side=<number>] define the number of pixels of the longest side.
[animation=false] skip animating the lines.
[mode=monotone] activate monotone mode.
[detail=<number 0‚Äì1>] coarser (0) or finer (1) lines, default: 0.5.

Press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold] to save the current frame.
	- in normal mode: PNG file.
	- in monotone mode: SVG file, suitable for plotting.

Note: The monotone SVG file has no defined dimensions. It is suitable for plotting at 30 √ó 30 cm. with a 0.25 mm. pen tip. When plotting in larger sizes, you can increase the [detail] parameter to keep contrast with the same pen.
